  "text": "Forest type stratification for changed areas.-To assess the type of forest affected by disturbances, we stratified 1994 and 2000 disturbed areas into broad-leaved forest, mixed forest, and coniferous forest based on the tasseled cap transformed 1988 Landsat image. To evaluate the accuracy of the forest type classification, we also included some areas of unchanged, mature forest where ground truth had been mapped [CITATION_1] and we used a stratified random sample of 250 such plots. We clustered the combined data set using ISODATA into 30 classes, which were labeled using expert knowledge and independent field data. Clouded areas in the 1988 image were classified using the same approach, but based on the 2 October 1986 image. Statistics were calculated based on the disturbed areas only. Disturbances in 1988 were not stratified into forest types due to the lack of ground-truth data for the MSS images.",
